{% block head_styles %}{% include 'partials/funder-styles.html.twig' %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <section class="masthead">
      <div class="shell">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Council</div>
          <h1 class="display">A small council, so First Nations<br>choose the systems<br>that serve them.</h1>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="lede">We author governance for Indigenous-led digital decisions and run three programs that put it into use. Everything on this site is shipped and dated.</p>
          <dl class="fund-facts">
            <dt>Status</dt><dd>Incorporating, not-for-profit</dd>
            <dt>Programs</dt><dd>3, all with shipped work</dd>
            <dt>Funds held</dt><dd>Trusteeship being arranged; named on the <a href="/support">Support page</a> before we accept funds</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec" id="programs">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="sec__head reveal">
          <div><div class="sec__num">01 · Programs</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="sec__title">Three programs. One premise.</h2>
            <p class="sec__intro">The systems meant to serve First Nations are rarely chosen by them. Each program puts that right in a different place. All three have shipped work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="fund-cards reveal">
          <article class="fund-card fund-card--flag">
            <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Language</span><span class="fund-card__badge">Flagship · in build</span></div>
            <h3><a href="/anishinaabemowin">Anishinaabemowin</a></h3>
            <p>Language revitalization with consent infrastructure: a curated corpus now, Lesson 1 in prototype, language games returning at relaunch, a talking doll now being built, and story nights to come.</p>
            <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/anishinaabemowin">$25k pilots the doll batch and a season of story nights &rarr;</a>
          </article>
          <article class="fund-card">
            <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Infrastructure</span></div>
            <h3><a href="/programs/anokii">Anokii</a></h3>
            <p>Community platforms on Waaseyaa, designed to be Nation-governed. Two OIATC-run reference vantages running, with a regional coverage plan ready to fund.</p>
            <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/anokii">Regional rollout, Sault to Manitoulin &rarr;</a>
          </article>
          <article class="fund-card">
            <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Knowledge</span></div>
            <h3><a href="/programs/community-knowledge">Community knowledge</a></h3>
            <p>Plain-language explainers for members: treaty annuities, the solar project, where your data lives.</p>
            <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/community-knowledge">Used by a local reporter &rarr;</a>
          </article>
        </div>
        <p class="reveal" style="margin-top: var(--gap-4); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-2); max-width: 74ch;">OIATC supports the independent, member-led Robinson Huron Treaty Members' <a href="https://rhtcircle.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: var(--accent-deep)">Transparency Circle</a>. We neither run it nor govern it.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec" id="proof">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="sec__head reveal">
          <div><div class="sec__num">02 · Proof, not slideware</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="sec__title">What exists today.</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="fund-proof reveal">
          <div><div class="fund-proof__n">27</div><div class="fund-proof__l">curated corpus items</div></div>
          <div><div class="fund-proof__n">20+</div><div class="fund-proof__l">pages shipped and dated</div></div>
          <div><div class="fund-proof__n">2</div><div class="fund-proof__l">platforms in active build</div></div>
          <div><div class="fund-proof__n">1st</div><div class="fund-proof__l">party analytics, no ad-tech</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec sec--statement" id="theory">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="sec__head reveal">
          <div><div class="sec__num">03 · Theory of change</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="sec__title">When communities choose and govern their digital systems, the systems fit. When the systems fit, services and language outcomes improve. We exist to make the first part true.</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec" id="support">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="sec__head reveal">
          <div><div class="sec__num">04 · Support</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="sec__title">Fund shipped work.</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="fund-support reveal">
          <div>
            <p class="body body--wide">We are early and honest about it: incorporating now, with a trusteeship arrangement being arranged before we accept funds. Each program page says exactly what the next dollar unlocks.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/support">Partner with OIATC &rarr;</a>
            <div class="fund-support__also">Also seeking: one more arm's-length director and a first partner Nation.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec" id="council">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="sec__head reveal">
          <div><div class="sec__num">05 · Council members</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="sec__title">A small council, held with care.</h2>
            <p class="sec__intro">The council today is deliberately small. Growth is gated on fit, not urgency. Full profiles live on the <a class="link" href="/about">About page</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-3 reveal">
          <article class="card">
            <div class="card__eyebrow">Council member</div>
            <h3>Russell Jones</h3>
            <p class="card__meta">Ojibwe from Sagamok Anishnawbek &middot; Founder &middot; Full-stack developer</p>
            <p class="body">In 2023 Russell was contracted to implement a case-management system at a First Nations Child and Family Advocacy Unit, saw within weeks that it would not fit the community, and made the case for a Canadian-built alternative already in use at neighbouring Nations. The recommendation was shelved and the contract ended. OIATC is how that lesson becomes a practice.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <div class="card__eyebrow">Council member</div>
            <h3><a class="link" href="https://web.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Networks</a></h3>
            <p class="card__meta">Est. 1987 &middot; One of Canada's first ISPs &middot; Non-profit worker co-op &middot; Canadian soil</p>
            <p class="body">A non-profit worker co-op whose clients have included the Legislative Assembly of Nunavut and Nunavut Public Library Services. Web Networks provides OIATC's hosting foundation and sits on the council.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <div class="card__eyebrow">Council member</div>
            <h3>Oliver Zielke</h3>
            <p class="card__meta">Director &middot; Non-profit technology</p>
            <p class="body">Former Director at Web Networks, with a background in non-profit and open-source technology. Joins the board as OIATC incorporates.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal" style="margin-top: var(--gap-5)">
          <article class="card">
            <div class="card__eyebrow">Elder &middot; Knowledge Keeper</div>
            <h3><a class="link" href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61582894730998" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steven Bennett</a></h3>
            <p class="card__meta">Fluent speaker of Anishinaabemowin</p>
            <p class="body">A fluent speaker who shares his teachings of Anishinaabemowin publicly. His recordings are the foundation of the language program, used with his agreement, and he guides the council on language and cultural knowledge.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec" id="contact" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="sec__head reveal">
          <div><div class="sec__num">06 · Contact</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="sec__title" id="contact-heading">jonesrussell42@gmail.com</h2>
            <p class="sec__intro">One seat is held by the founder. Writing to Russell is writing to OIATC.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="actions reveal">
          <a class="btn btn--primary" href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">Email Russell &rarr;</a>
          <a class="btn btn--secondary" href="/support">Partner with OIATC</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
{% endblock %}
